                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1087: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-25T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1920—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Your March 22, 9 a.m.</p>
                <p>What proportion of one three hundred sixty fifth do daily deposits amount to.
                    Department has requested Consul Guayaquil to make weekly inquiry as to deposits
                    and suggest that you visit Guayaquil and familiarize yourself with Governments
                    methods of making deposits. Cable full report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
